Society.Relationships:
[[File:Pixie grig brownie dm-420 beth trott.jpg|thumb|right|250px|''A [[brownie]] romances a sylph, as a [[pixie]] watches and a [[grig]] fiddler serenades,  surrounded by [[fireflies]].'']]
Some were known to befriend adventurers and even aid them in exchange for favors, though in general, they distanced themselves from mundane races. They were most often seen in the company of [[dryad]]s and nymphs.{{Cite dragon/155/Folk of the Faerie Kingdom|38}}<ref group="note">This information is sourced from [[Dragon magazine 155|''Dragon'' #155]], pp. 30–41. That article presents an alternative Queen of Faeries named Rhiannon, who shares many similarities with Titania but also some differences. All other 2{{nd}}-edition sources, however, refer instead to Titania. Others were known to serve the [[Archomental]] Princess of Good of [[Air]], [[Chan]].{{Cite dragon/353/Princes of Elemental Good|47}}

Sylphs were also known to trade with other creatures for light furnishings for their nests, such as silks and pillows.
